Elder-Beerman Stores Corp saidowners of about 70 pct of its stock have offered to take thecompany private by offerring 30 dlrs per share for theremaining 30 pct of its stock.    The company said the proposal will be considered at aregularly scheduled board meeting on March 17.    It said the offer was made by members of the Beerman familyholding about 70 pct of the company's stock, Chairman MaxGutmann, and certain members of the board. Reuter&#3;